meanings.definition: (archaic) third-person singular present of wrassle; to wrestle
meanings.english_definition: (archaic) Third-person singular simple present indicative form of wrassle.

etymology.value: Archaic form of 'wrestles'. See 'wrestle' for etymology.

usage_notes.explanation: This is an archaic form of the word 'wrestles', the third-person singular present tense of the verb 'wrestle'. It is rarely used in modern English.

readability_explanation.text: This is an archaic form and not commonly used in modern English. It is more likely to be encountered in older literature.
